<div id="review_2727791135" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2727791135" />
    <a title="Christopher Saunders" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/13546014-christopher-saunders"><img alt="Christopher Saunders" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1642974439p2/13546014.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2727791135?book_show_action=true">Feb 25, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Christopher Saunders" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Christopher Saunders" href="/user/show/13546014-christopher-saunders">Christopher Saunders</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13546014-christopher-saunders?shelf=2019-reads">2019-reads</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/13546014-christopher-saunders?shelf=avocado-recs">avocado-recs</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2727791135" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17112185822844827987">Charles C. Mann&apos;s <b>1493</b> examines the impact of European colonization of the New World in a variety of fashions. Mann makes the argument that the Columbian Exchange was one of the Earth&apos;s most important events, with impacts both immediate and long-term, obvious and subtle. Not only white conquest and settlement (and the destruction of Native cultures) but the establishment of slavery, which in turn stimulated modern capitalism and devastated the African continent; not only disease and technology b</span>
  <span id="freeText17112185822844827987" style="display:none">Charles C. Mann's <b>1493</b> examines the impact of European colonization of the New World in a variety of fashions. Mann makes the argument that the Columbian Exchange was one of the Earth's most important events, with impacts both immediate and long-term, obvious and subtle. Not only white conquest and settlement (and the destruction of Native cultures) but the establishment of slavery, which in turn stimulated modern capitalism and devastated the African continent; not only disease and technology but the exchange of animals and crops with a truly worldwide impact, shifting entire ecosystems and uprooting human habits at once. Thus people, not only in Europe but Asia, Africa and the Middle East, found themselves reaping the benefits and drawbacks of a truly global economy: growing addicted to tobacco, sugar and coffee, refocusing cuisine and culture around maize and potatoes, valuing stimulated trade and capital as marks of "progress." It's all written in a surprisingly accessible fashion, with Mann juggling his various disciplines and approaches with enviable ease. </span>
  <a data-text-id="17112185822844827987" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


